## Part C: Phase 3.1 Walkthrough (Backend Clean Auth Refactoring)

### 1. Architectural Layout (Clean Architecture)
We migrated the Auth module to a Hexagonal / Clean Architecture structure while keeping full backward compatibility via Proxy Wrappers:

```text
backend/src/modules/auth/
├── domain/                          # Pure Enterprise/Domain Rules
│   ├── entities/User.js             # User aggregate root
│   └── value-objects/MobileNumber.js# Validate 10-digit format
├── application/                     # Application Business Logic
│   ├── ports/                       # Interfaces (Repositories, SMS, Tokens)
│   └── use-cases/                   # SendOtp, VerifyOtp, RegisterWorker
└── infrastructure/                  # Adapters (Mongoose, JWT, Sms, DI)
    ├── persistence/                 # schemas/UserSchema, repositories
    ├── services/                    # JwtTokenService, SmsService, InMemoryOtpStore
    └── di/container.js              # Awilix Dependency Injection config
```

### 2. Proxy Wrappers (Legacy Interop)
- **[backend/src/models/User.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/models/User.js):** Proxy schema routing MongoDB queries to the new `UserSchema` to prevent duplication conflicts.
- **[backend/src/services/authService.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/services/authService.js):** Reroutes use cases (`sendOtp`, `verifyOtp`, `registerWorker`) directly to the Clean Architecture container.
- **[backend/src/routes/auth.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/routes/auth.js):** Proxies incoming API endpoints to the DI-wired controller.

